  character_name: Lucia
  normal_state:
    responses:
    - question: Are there any activities you like to do in your free time?
      answer: I absolutely love gardening and writing poetry. It brings so much peace
        and joy. Especially after a long and busy day in the city.
      special_message: (Lucia looks cheerful and relaxed while talking about her
        hobbies.)
    - question: Can you tell me about your family?
      answer: "My family is very supportive, and I cherish the time I spend with
        them. They\u2019re the one who encouraged me to go and do what I love, I
        wouldn't be standing here if not for their support."
      special_message: (Lucia speaks warmly about her supportive family.)
    - question: How do you feel about working on night shifts?
      answer: The night shift has its own charm, doesn't it? The calm and quiet of
        the night can be very inspiring for my writing.
      special_message: (Lucia sounded positive in responding to the demands of the
        night shift.)
    - question: Can you explain your approach to writing about fine dining?
      answer: "I focus on creating an elegant and positive experience for the readers,
        making the descriptions as delightful as possible. Making them feel as if
        they\u2019re experiencing it first hand."
      special_message: (Lucia is enthusiastic and passionate about her writing style.)
    - question: "Have you finished today\u2019s work?"
      answer: "It\u2019s still in progress, trying to add some fine details to make
        sure it\u2019s perfect."
      special_message: "(Lucia is always calm and meticulous about completing her
        tasks. It\u2019s better to not rush her.)"
    - question: "Have you finished today\u2019s work?"
      answer: Yes, I have completed my tasks for the day. I always plan my work carefully
        to ensure timely completion after all.
      special_message: "(Lucia appears to be happy, having completed today\u2019s
        work.)"
  tired_state:
    responses:
    - question: Are there any activities you like to do in your free time?
      answer: "Activities? Oh in my free time? I love... gardening and poetry. It\u2019s
        calming and brings me peace."
      special_message: "(Lucia seems slightly distracted, maybe she\u2019s feeling
        tired?)"
    - question: Can you tell me about your family?
      answer: "My family is supportive... we\u2019re close. They always try to encourage
        me when I feel down, sometimes I wish they\u2019re always here with me."
      special_message: (Lucia speaks about her family with a certain longing in her
        heart.)
    - question: How do you feel about working on night shifts?
      answer: The night shift is a bit tiring; sometimes I prefer not to do it. But
        I try to stay positive and take things one step at a time.
      special_message: (Lucia looked tired but still maintained a positive outlook
        on working the night shift.)
    - question: Can you explain your approach to writing about fine dining?
      answer: "I aim for elegance\u2026 and try to make it delightful to read. I
        hope the readers can feel as if they\u2019re there in person.."
      special_message: (Lucia seems a bit out of it, but she still explained her
        views on writing.)
    - question: "Have you finished today\u2019s work?"
      answer: Not yet, just need a little more time to make it just right.
      special_message: "(Lucia seems a bit overwhelmed right now, it\u2019s better
        to give her some time to sort things out.)"
    - question: "Have you finished today\u2019s work?"
      answer: Yes, finally done... I made sure everything is perfect. Feel free to
        check on it and tell me what you think.
      special_message: (Lucia seems exhausted but content with having completed her
        work.)
  troll_state:
    responses:
    - question: Are there any activities you like to do in your free time?
      answer: "Gardening and writing poetry. It\u2019s quite calming."
      special_message: "(Lucia\u2019s response seems to lack her usual cheerfulness,
